# Onshape Users, Teams, Companies & Accounts

The identity layer of the Onshape API: who you are (`/users`), the groups you
belong to (`/teams`, `/companies`), and what your org has paid for
(`/accounts`). These resources are the **principals** that documents are shared
with (see @onshape/documents) and the IDs that ACLs and webhooks reference.

Unlike geometry, none of these endpoints use the `did/wid/eid` path — they are
flat resources keyed by `uid` (user), `tid` (team), `cid` (company), and
`planId`/`aid`/`pid` (account/purchase).

## Model

- A **user** (`uid`) is the authenticated principal. `GET /users/sessioninfo`
  returns the session's identity — the cheapest authenticated call and the
  canonical auth smoke test (@onshape/auth).
- A user belongs to zero or more **companies** (`cid`) and **teams** (`tid`).
  A team can be company-owned. Membership is the join: `GET /teams` lists the
  current user's teams; `GET /companies` lists the current user's companies;
  `GET /companies/{cid}/users` and `GET /teams/{tid}/members` enumerate the
  other direction.
- **Roles & permissions** live on the company edge: a company user carries
  `admin`, `guest`, `light`, and `globalPermissions[]` (integer codes). These
  are the principals + permissions an ACL grants document access to.
- An **account** owns **purchases** (`BTPurchaseInfo`) under a **plan**
  (`planId`) — seats, API allocation, subscription state.
- `sessioninfo` is the cheapest auth-check call: no IDs needed, returns the
  signed-in identity; assert a `name`/`id` comes back to confirm credentials.

## Endpoints

Users
- `POST /users/session` — authenticate credentials, create a session (browser
  flow; production code uses API keys, see @onshape/auth).
- `GET  /users/sessioninfo` — session identity for the signed-in user. **Auth check.**
- `GET  /users/settings` — settings for the signed-in user; `?includematerials`.
- `GET  /users/{uid}/settings` — settings for any org user (admins only).

Teams
- `GET /teams` — teams the current user belongs to. Filters: `query`, `filter`,
  `uid`, `companyId`, `sortColumn`, `sortOrder`, `includeCompanyOwnedTeams`,
  `offset`, `limit`. Paged (`items`/`next`/`previous`).
- `GET /teams/{tid}` — one team's info.
- `GET /teams/{tid}/members` — team members; `sortColumn`, `sortOrder`, `q`,
  `offset`, `limit`. Paged.

Companies
- `GET    /companies` — companies the user belongs to; `uid`, `activeOnly`, `includeAll`. Paged.
- `GET    /companies/{cid}` — company info (address, admin, domainPrefix, ownerId, purchase…).
- `GET    /companies/{cid}/documentsbyname` — find a doc by exact `name`.
- `GET    /companies/{cid}/users` — company members; `q`, `roleFilter`,
  `includeGlobalPermissions`, `afterDateAdded`, `beforeDateAdded`, paging. Paged.
- `POST   /companies/{cid}/users` — add a user (write).
- `POST   /companies/{cid}/users/{uid}` — update a user's company info (write).
- `DELETE /companies/{cid}/users/{uid}` — remove a user; `removeFromTeams`, `removeDirectShares` (write).
- `POST   /companies/{cid}/globalpermission/{type}/{id}` — grant global permissions to a user/team (write).
- `DELETE /companies/{cid}/globalpermission/{type}/{id}` — revoke; `?permission` (write).

Accounts
- `GET    /accounts/purchases` — app purchases by the current user; `all`, `ownPurchaseOnly`.
- `GET    /accounts/plans/{planId}/purchases` — purchases for a plan; `offset`, `limit`. Paged.
- `POST   /accounts/purchases/{pid}/consume` — mark a purchase consumed (write).
- `DELETE /accounts/{aid}/purchases/{pid}` — cancel a subscription; `?cancelImmediately` (write).

## Shapes

`GET /teams` — paged list (same envelope for `/companies`, `/teams/{tid}/members`,
`/companies/{cid}/users`):

```json
{
  "href": "https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10/teams",
  "items": [ { /* BTTeamInfo */ } ],
  "next": "…", "previous": "…"
}
```

`GET /companies/{cid}` — company info (meaningful fields):

```json
{
  "id": "string",
  "name": "string",
  "description": "string",
  "domainPrefix": "string",
  "ownerId": "string",
  "admin": true,
  "address": { /* BTAddressInfo */ },
  "purchase": { /* BTPurchaseInfo */ },
  "state": 0, "type": 0,
  "href": "string"
}
```

`POST /companies/{cid}/users` — add-user request body; the company-user response
carries the role flags an ACL cares about:

```json
// request
{ "email": "string", "admin": false, "guest": false, "light": false,
  "globalPermissions": [0], "companyId": "string" }
// response (BTCompanyUserInfo): role edge on user ↔ company
{ "id": "string", "name": "string", "admin": false, "guest": false,
  "light": false, "company": { /* BTCompanySummaryInfo */ },
  "user": { /* BTUserBasicSummaryInfo */ }, "userRolePriority": { },
  "state": 0, "lastLoginTime": "string", "href": "string" }
```

## Recipe

Read-only auth smoke test — `GET /users/sessioninfo` with Basic auth, then
verify identity came back. This is the credential check referenced by
@onshape/auth. **READ-ONLY** (no writes despite the write endpoints above).

```bash
# needs ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY + ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY (dev-portal.onshape.com key pair)
# Basic auth over HTTPS — local testing form; production uses HMAC, see @onshape/auth
BASE=https://cad.onshape.com/api/v10

resp=$(curl -fsS -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" \
  -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  "$BASE/users/sessioninfo")

# verify: a name/id must come back, else creds are bad
echo "$resp" | python3 -c 'import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); \
  assert d.get("name") or d.get("id"), "no identity in sessioninfo — auth failed"; \
  print("auth OK:", d.get("name") or d.get("id"))'
```

Follow-on read-only calls (same Basic auth) — list teams, then resolve members:

```bash
curl -fsS -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" "$BASE/teams"
# pick a tid from items[], then:
curl -fsS -u "$ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY:$ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY" "$BASE/teams/$TID/members"
```

